# Maintain README

When you change anything a user or contributor would notice, update `README.md` in the same change (do not wait to be asked).

## Update when

- Adding, renaming, or removing a world preset / generator
- Changing install steps, `level-type` IDs, or pack format / Minecraft target
- Changing local test script, VS Code tasks, or release workflow behavior
- Changing adventure biome whitelist policy or other documented design intent
- Changing repo layout that the README describes

## Do not

- Paste long biome lists into the README when a tag/file path already documents them — link the file instead
- Rewrite the whole README for a small change; edit only the affected sections
- Add marketing fluff or unrelated docs
